      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A p0171 code, indicating a lean condition, can be tricky, but let's see if we can find the root cause. If the Mass Air Flow (MAF) sensor is in good shape, we might need to investigate other areas. First, check the fuel injectors; they might be clogged or not delivering the right amount of fuel. Also, inspect the fuel pressure regulator and fuel pump. If the fuel pressure is too low, it could cause a lean condition. Lastly, don't forget to check for any vacuum leaks, as they can also lead to a lean condition. Good luck, and may the spirits of the ancient, wise, and mischievous goblins guide you on your quest to fix your trusty steed!",
